Eleven person abducted by bandits in Zamfara State have been freed. They were kidnapped at Wanzamai village in Tsafe Local Government Area of the state. Their rescue was facilitated by the police and a peace committee set up by the state government, police spokesman Muhammad Shehu said yesterday. The victims, all indigenes of Katsina State, were snatched by armed bandits while returning from a market on a bus. They were taken to the forest from where their rescuers freed them. They were in good health, it was learnt